com.sun.xml.ws.commons.virtualbox
Class IISCSIHardDisk

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.xml.ws.commons.virtualbox.IISCSIHardDisk

public class IISCSIHardDisk
extends Object

THe IISCSIHardDisk interface represents a specific type of IHardDisk that uses iSCSI. The IISCSIHardDisk interface represents IHardDisk that use the Internet SCSI (iSCSI) protocol to store hard disk data on remote machines. Objects that support this interface also support the IHardDisk interface. iSCSI hard disks can be created using IVirtualBox#createHardDisk(). When a new hard disk object is created, all its properties are uninitialized. After you assign some meaningful values to them, the hard disk object can be registered by calling IVirtualBox#registerHardDisk() and then IMachine#attachHardDisk() to virtual machines. The IHardDisk#description of the iSCSI hard disk is stored in the VirtualBox configuration file, so it can be changed (at appropriate times) even when IHardDisk#accessible returnsfalse. However, the hard disk must not be attached to a running virtual machine.

In the current imlementation, the type of all iSCSI hard disks is HardDiskType#Writethrough and cannot be changed.
